{"title_page": "Dow University of Health Sciences", "text_new": "{{Infobox university\n| name              =Dow University of Health Sciences\n| native_name       = \u0688\u0627\u0626\u0648 \u06cc\u0648\u0646\u06cc\u0648\u0633\u0679\u06cc \u0622\u0641 \u06c1\u06cc\u0644\u062a\u06be \u0633\u0627\u0626\u0646\u0633\n| image             =DUHS-Logo.gif\n| image_size        =\n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = \n| latin_name        = \n| motto             = \n| motto_lang        = \n| mottoeng          =''Prevention Is Better than Cure.'' \n| established       = {{Start date|1945}}\n| closed            = <!-- {{End date|YYYY}} -->\n| type              =[[Public university|Public]] \n| parent            = \n| affiliation       = \n| endowment         = \n| budget            = \n| officer_in_charge = \n| chairman          = \n| chancellor        = [[Imran Ismail]], [[Governor of Sindh]] \n| president         = \n| vice-president    = \n| superintendent    = \n| provost           = \n| vice_chancellor   =\n| CEO            = \n| principal         = \n| dean              = \n| director          = \n| head_label        =Registrar  \n| head              =Aman ullah abbasi<ref name=\"Registrar office of Dow University\">{{cite web|last=Office of the Registrar|title=Office of the Registrar|url=http://www.duhs.edu.pk/news/Notice%20Of%20Reschedule%20-%20DUHSHR201302%20dated%2008-12-2013.pdf|work=Registrar office of Dow University|publisher=Registrar office of Dow University|accessdate=31 March 2014|format=PDF}}</ref>    \n| academic_staff    = \n| administrative_staff = \n| students          =\n| undergrad         =\n| postgrad          =\n| doctoral          =\n| other             = \n| city              =[[Karachi]] \n| state             = \n| province          =[[Sindh, Pakistan|Sindh]] \n| country           =[[Pakistan]] \n| coor              = \n| campus            =[[Urban area|Urban]]\n| former_names      = \n| free_label        = \n| free              = \n| colours        = {{scarf|start}}{{cell|#062A78}}{{cell|#ED9121}}{{cell|#FFFFFF}}{{scarf|end}} \n| athletics         = \n| sports            = \n| nickname          ='''DUHS'''\n| mascot            = \n| affiliations      =[[Higher Education Commission (Pakistan)|HEC]], [[Pakistan Medical Research Council|PMRC]] \n| website           ={{URL|http://www.duhs.edu.pk/}}\n| logo              = \n| footnotes         = \n}}\n\nThe '''Dow University of Health Sciences''' ([[Acronym and initialism|initials]]: '''DUHS''') {{lang-ur|{{nq|'''\u0688\u0627\u0626\u0648 \u06cc\u0648\u0646\u06cc\u0648\u0633\u0679\u06cc \u0622\u0641 \u06c1\u06cc\u0644\u062a\u06be \u0633\u0627\u0626\u0646\u0633'''}}}}), is one of the oldest public sector universities in Pakistan. It is located in the [[Urban area|urban]] metropolitan area of [[Karachi]], [[Sindh, Pakistan|Sindh]], [[Pakistan]].<ref name=\"Google maps, inc\">{{cite web|last=Google|title=Address of the Dow University of Health Sciences|url=https://maps.google.com/maps?q=university+of+education+college+road+township+lahore&ie=UTF-8&ei=hg05U520LcjOqAGS1oGQCw&ved=0CAgQ_AUoAw|work=Google maps, inc|publisher=Google maps, inc|accessdate=31 March 2014}}</ref> The university comprises two health sciences undergraduate research institutes: [[Dow Medical College]] and Dow international Medical College. The University also has a very strong department of Postgraduate studies which monitors various basic medical sciences and clinical sciences programs at DUHS.\n\nEstablished in 1945 as the Dow Medical College, it is known for its strong emphasis on  economics [[Biomedical engineering|biomedical]], [[Health sciences|health]], and [[Medical research|medical]] research programmes.<ref name=\"Admissions\"/> It is ranked among the top medical schools by [[Higher Education Commission (Pakistan)|HEC]] in 2010, 2011, 2012, 2013 and 2014.<ref name=\"HEC Rankings\">{{cite web|last=HEC Rankings|title=HEC Rankings|url=http://www.hec.gov.pk/INSIDEHEC/DIVISIONS/QALI/OTHERS/RANKINGOFUNIVERSITIES/Pages/CategoryWise.aspx|publisher=HEC Rankings|accessdate=31 March 2014|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130525073744/http://www.hec.gov.pk/InsideHEC/Divisions/QALI/Others/RankingofUniversities/Pages/CategoryWise.aspx|archivedate=25 May 2013}}</ref> The university is named after its founder, Sir [[Hugh Dow]], who laid the foundation of the institution in 1945.<ref name=\"History of DUHS\">{{cite web|title=History of DUHS|url=http://www.duhs.edu.pk/inner.php?button=introduction|publisher=History of DUHS|accessdate=31 March 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140402133158/http://www.duhs.edu.pk/inner.php?button=introduction|archive-date=2 April 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>  The institution offers [[undergraduate]], [[post-graduate]] and [[Doctoral Program|doctoral]] programmes in almost all academic disciplines relating to [[medical science]]s.<ref name=\"Admissions\">{{cite web|last=Programmes at DUHS|title=Programmes at DUHS|url=http://www.duhs.edu.pk/inner.php?button=academic|work=Admissions|publisher=Admissions|accessdate=31 March 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140402125141/http://www.duhs.edu.pk/inner.php?button=academic|archive-date=2 April 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref> \n\nDow university also got involved in \"condom controversy, when private condom company called josh advertized their contraceptives.[https://www.mangobaaz.com/someone-got-pissed-that-a-university-in-karachi-celebrated-world-contraception-day-so-pakistanis-schooled-them]\n\n==Academics==\n\nPharm-D (5 Year Duration) at Dow College of Pharmacy\nDow Institute of Medical Technology<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.duhs.edu.pk/inner.php?button=imt|title=Welcome to Dow University of Health Sciences|author=|date=|website=www.duhs.edu.pk|access-date=2014-10-22|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180409185227/http://www.duhs.edu.pk/inner.php?button=imt|archive-date=2018-04-09|url-status=dead}}</ref> offers four-year Bachelor's programs in four disciplines: Clinical Pathology Technology, Surgical Technology, Respiratory and Critical Care Technology and Ophthalmology.\n\n==Journals==\n\nThe Journal of the Dow University of Health Science [http://www.jduhs.com] is published 4 monthly by Dow University of Health Sciences. It is recognised by Pakistan Medical and Dental Council and indexed in IMEMR, Pakmedinet and Global Health. It is also available as an online medical journal. \n\nEl Mednifico Journal (''EISSN 2307-7301'') is  an open access, quarterly, peer-reviewed, international medical journal.{{Citation needed|date=April 2020}} \n\nThe Journal of Pakistan Medical Students [http://www.jpmsonline.com] is a peer-reviewed, international journal from the students of Dow Medical College. It was started by Anis Rehman and Haris Riaz, from Batch of 2011.{{Citation needed|date=April 2020}}\n\n==Social service activities==\n[[Patients' Welfare Association]], also known as PWA, is one of the largest and oldest student run volunteer NGO of Pakistan. Students of Dow Medical College have been managing it since 1979. The organization is a blessing for the poor patients coming to Civil Hospital Karachi, helping them through its Blood Bank, Drug Bank, Thalassemia Services, and General and Tuberculosis Follow-Up Clinics.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.pwa-chk.org|title=\u30a2\u30b3\u30e0\u3067\u304a\u91d1\u3092\u501f\u308a\u308b\uff01\u3010\u5373\u65e5\u5be9\u67fb\u3001\u632f\u8fbc\u2026\u3069\u3046\u3059\u308c\u3070\u53ef\u80fd\uff1f\u3011|author=|date=|website=www.pwa-chk.org}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/pwachk|title=Patients' Welfare Association-PWA|author=|date=|website=www.facebook.com}}</ref> It has been cited in press for its earnest efforts in free patient service<ref>\"Volunteers at college\" in Daily [[Dawn (newspaper)]] By Dr Masroor H.S. Bukhari, November 22, 2009.</ref>\n\n==Research & Development==\nResearch at Dow University has discovered some variants of human gene, which may provide potency for fighting against [[Coronavirus disease 2019]], as the sequence of  virus in Pakistan is somewhat different from the [[Severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2|Wuhan virus]] with few mutations<ref>{{cite web|author=Imtiaz Ali|url=https://www.dawn.com/news/1547823 |title=Human gene variants may offer resistance against Covid-19, Dow research suggests|publisher= Dawn |date=9 April 2020 |accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Khurshid Ahmed|url=https://www.arabnews.pk/node/1654011/pakistan|title=Pakistani scientists get government nod to develop coronavirus vaccine|publisher= Arab News Pakistan|date=6 April 2020|accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\nTeam of scientists at Karachi has earlier found and identified 9 gene compounds and their efficiency in controlling the growth of epidemic virus <ref>{{cite news\n| last = Rizvi | first = Safdar| last2 = | first2 = | title = Scientists in Karachi may have identified compounds effective in inhibiting growth of COVID-19 in host cells| work = The Express Tribune| date = 22 March 2020| url = https://tribune.com.pk/story/2181264/1-scientists-karachi-may-identified-compounds-effective-inhibiting-growth-covid-19-host-cells/| access-date = 13 April 2020 }}</ref>. On 13 April, Research team of Dow University disclosed that the DUHS finds a ray of hope in combating [[COVID-19]] epidemic, by suggesting local [[Immunoglobulin therapy|IVIG]] from recovered  patients holds the potential to control the progress of virus in host (infected).  They pointed out that this treatment process involves minimum risk with desired efficacy in recovering from COVID-19.<ref>{{cite web|author=Mohammad Bilal Tahir|url= https://www.brecorder.com/2020/04/13/588906/pakistan-scientists-achieve-significant-breakthrough-in-the-fight-against-covid-19/ |title= Pakistan scientists achieve significant breakthrough in the fight against COVID-19 |publisher= Business Recorder|date=13 April 2020 |accessdate=13 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.duhs.edu.pk/ Dow University of Health Sciences \u2013 Official website]\n* [http://www.brecorder.com/index.php?id=669007&currPageNo=1&query=&search=&term=&supDate= Complete Profile \u2013 Business Recorder.com]\n* [https://myhotnewspk.com/pakistan-scientists-achieve-significant-breakthrough-in-the-fight-against-covid-19/ significant breakthrough against COVID-19]\n* {{coord missing|Karachi}}\n{{Medical schools in Pakistan}}\n{{Colleges and universities in Karachi}}\n{{Dow University of Health Sciences}}\n{{Karachi}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Dow University Of Health Sciences}}\n[[Category:Public universities and colleges in Sindh]]\n[[Category:Medical colleges in Sindh]]\n[[Category:Cancer organizations]]\n[[Category:HIV/AIDS research organisations]]\n[[Category:Universities and colleges in Karachi]]\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1945]]\n[[Category:Dow University of Health Sciences| ]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox university\n| name              =Dow University of Health Sciences\n| native_name       = \u0688\u0627\u0626\u0648 \u06cc\u0648\u0646\u06cc\u0648\u0633\u0679\u06cc \u0622\u0641 \u06c1\u06cc\u0644\u062a\u06be \u0633\u0627\u0626\u0646\u0633\n| image             =DUHS-Logo.gif\n| image_size        =\n| image_alt         = \n| caption           = \n| latin_name        = \n| motto             = \n| motto_lang        = \n| mottoeng          =''Prevention Is Better than Cure.'' \n| established       = {{Start date|1945}}\n| closed            = <!-- {{End date|YYYY}} -->\n| type              =[[Public university|Public]] \n| parent            = \n| affiliation       = \n| endowment         = \n| budget            = \n| officer_in_charge = \n| chairman          = \n| chancellor        = [[Imran Ismail]], [[Governor of Sindh]] \n| president         = \n| vice-president    = \n| superintendent    = \n| provost           = \n| vice_chancellor   =\n| CEO            = \n